"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1929447-Olympics-2024-medal-ceremonies-cardboard-boxes\", \"text\": \"  It's not just gold, silver, and bronze medals that athletes are receiving on the podiums at the2024 Paris Olympics. With the action at the summer Games now well underway, more than 30 events have already been decided withTeam GB winning their first gold on Monday in the team equestrian.  The medals have been specially designed, with a hexagonal piece of the Eiffel Tower set into the mementoes.  The iron fragments were removed from the tower and preserved during renovations before the turn of the century, and have now been used to add\\u00a0a\\u00a0historic element to the medals.  Pick up your ultimate guide to the Olympics! Going for Gold provides the day-by-day rundown of what's on and when. Clickhereto buy.  A toy version of the Paris 2024 official mascot, the red Olympic Phryge, is also being handed out. And in addition, viewers have noted that top-three finishers have been receiving small brown boxes, prompting debate over what was actually in them.  It's been revealed that the boxes, which are around 40 centimetres long, all contain a\\u00a0rolled-up\\u00a0copy of the official Paris 2024 Olympic poster. Designed and drawn by famous Parisian illustrator Ugo Gattoni, the poster is nothing if not unique.  The image depicts a cartoon version of Paris with the words \\\"XXXIII Olympiade,\\\" referencing that France is hosting the 33rd edition of the Summer Games. The River Seine and red Eiffel Tower also feature on the poster.    Discovery+is the new home of the Olympics. The streamer is set to broadcast 3,800 hours of sport live from Paris.  Sports fans can getDiscovery+ for \\u00a33.99a month until the end of 2024 via Amazon Prime's video channels. This also comes with anAmazon Prime 30-day free trial.  A diver has also been drawn into the bottom right corner, appearing to be watching on as the Olympic spectacle unfolds. The posters were unveiled in\\u00a0March\\u00a0and went on show for a week at the Mus\\u00e9e d'Orsay.  \\\"It's a new, key moment in the Paris 2024 story,\\\" said Paris 2024 president Tony Estanguet at the\\u00a0event. \\\"We have tried to be different and imagine posters that look like us, posters that go beyond a mere logo.\\\"  Gattoni reportedly spent more than 2,000 hours creating the poster. He is also renowned for writing the book Bicycle in 2012, the year of the London Olympics, which included images of a mass cycle race taking place in the English capital.  Do not miss:BBC Olympics coverage blasted as Nadal vs Djokovic ditched for Team GB thrashing  Do not miss:Furious BBC viewers switch off Paris Olympics issuing same complaint  Do not miss:Humphries has made passionate Olympics darts plea and put two events on notice  We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you. This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding. You can unsubscribe at any time. Read ourPrivacy Policy  Overall, 329 medal events will take place during the Olympic Games. The ceremonies are taking place at a variety of competition venues, with organisers maintaining the tradition of raising the national flag of each medal winner.  Team GB's first medal came early on Saturday morning\\u00a0after Yasmin Harper and Scarlett Mew Jensen claimed diving bronze. The total is now up to six - three silver, two bronze and one gold.  SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.  EXPRESS.CO.UK  Daily Express uses notifications to keep you updated\"}"